</font></big><p align='center'><strong><font color='#0E024D' face='Arial'><big>MAGICIAN FAQ</big></font></strong></p>
<div align='center'><center>

<table border='0' cellpadding='5' cellspacing='0' width='80%'>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><small><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><strong>Why
    do my summoned items disappear after I log?</strong></font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>All summoned items that a magician
    can conjure are only good till the user logs off. You can no longer store summoned items
    in the bank either. Anything you have that is summoned is history after you log off/get
    dropped. </font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><strong><small>Does
    my pet dual wield?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>The answer is yes - but they dual
    wield with their hands.&nbsp; As your pets gets higher in levels through higher summons
    they get both dual wield and double attack.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><strong><small>How
    do I make my pet wield a weapon?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>You can give you pet weapons by simply handing them to them.  After a while your pets can also wield two weapons.  They can be different weapons, or the same type.  Your pet will NOT dual wield unless it is wielding two weapons.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><strong><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small>Why
    won't my pet respond to it's commands?</small></font></strong></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>A magician's pet has to be within a
    certain range of the mage to receive the commands. Until recently the distance required
    was very close but the range was further increased to make it easier.&nbsp; Experiment
    around to find the distance to get to know it. </font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><strong><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small>I
    tell my pet to back off but it keeps fighting...why?</small></font></strong></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>The pet will receive the command
    and attempt to back off but will not back off if it is getting hit. For a pet to
    successfully back off of fighting a mob it must not get hit in the process.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><strong><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small>Where's
    the slime pet?</small></font></strong></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>Sorry, no slime pet in existence -
    and no there isn't one planned.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><strong><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small>How
    come the mobs always go for me and not my pet?</small></font></strong></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>Simply because you are nuking your
    target too much. A magician has to learn when to nuke and what nuke to use at the right
    times. Doing too much damage at once will cause the mob to aggro on you and will ignore
    your pet. Your pet needs to dish out extended damage as well as take extended damage. </small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><strong><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small>Nobody
    ever wants me in their group and take necros and wizards before me. Why aren't I loved?</small></font></strong></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>Magicians are one of the most
    little-known about classes in the game. Many do not realize how much a magician's pet can
    help out with damage and that we have great damage shields, which are great to put on any
    tank in your group. Magicians are also equipped with a great debuff spells
    (malise/malisement) and not to mention our ability to summon our many items, which now
    have some decent stats/effect. Everquest just needs more time till everyone fully realizes
    what a magician is fully capable of. </small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><strong><small>What
    should I specialise in?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>Take a look at the magician section
    of the specialisation guide.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><small><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><strong>How
    come my pets differ in levels all the time?</strong></font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>When summoning a pet it differs in
    levels with a 4-5 level spread. Sometimes they will con green, some blue, etc. This is
    where the spell 'reclaim energy' comes in handy as you can keep summoning a pet till you
    get one you are happy with. </small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><strong><small>What
    kind of armor can I wear?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>You can wear any armour which is
    cloth based.&nbsp; This also includes robes.&nbsp; </font></small><p><small><font
    face='Arial'>Magicians can also acquire their specialist Apothic Armor from the Plane of
    Hate.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><strong><small>Can
    I heal my pet?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>Yes you can both heal and buff your
    pet.&nbsp; Always try and get a cleric to give your pet a HP buff.  Burnout has also been siginifcantly upgraded since December 1999 and is now an excellent speed buff.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><strong><small>Where
    do I get my research book?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>Your research book can be bought
    from your guild.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><strong><small>Where
    do I get research components?</small></strong></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>Research components can be found on
    the corpses of the enemies you slay.&nbsp; You can also buy them off players who have
    found them as loot.&nbsp; Most components are found through trading.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small><strong>When
    I cast a AE spell such as rain of spikes, it never hits for 3 waves of full damage. Why?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>AE spells such as these are still
    in full functionality and yet will rarely hit for 3 waves of full damage like they are
    supposed to. Dodgy huh?</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small><strong>Where
    can I buy the summoning item spells? (eg summon heatstone, summon dagger of symbols)</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>All these spells are sold from
    different vendors than the ones magicians usually to at their guilds. These spells can be
    bought in the libraries in Neriak, Erudin and Ak'anon.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small><strong>Where
    are all my elemental pet spells? I can only find certain ones</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>Not all elemental pets are sold for
    each level. There is at least one elemental pet for every level though. The rest must be
    attained by research. </small></font></td>
  </tr>
</table>
</center></div><div align='center'><center>

<table border='0' cellpadding='5' cellspacing='0' width='80%'>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small><strong>My
    Pet committed suicide and slashed itself for 32000 damage.&nbsp; Why?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>There are a number of different
    things which you can do that will result in the death of your pet.&nbsp; If you hide or go
    invisible your pet will die.&nbsp; If you zone your pet will die.&nbsp; If you get
    invisible against undead or camouflage this will also kill your pet.&nbsp; Your pet will
    not die simply because you get too far away from it or it gets stuck.&nbsp; </small></font></td>
  </tr>
</table>
</center></div><div align='center'><center>

<table border='0' cellpadding='5' cellspacing='0' width='80%'>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small><strong>My
    pet has run off should I be afraid?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><small><font face='Arial'>Yes.&nbsp; Especially in dungeons.
    &nbsp; If your pet runs off chasing a monster or wanders too far then it may very well
    bring back friends.&nbsp; If it gets in a fight and dies then the monsters it was fighting
    will come for you.&nbsp; In short, don't let your pet out of your sight.&nbsp; It's better
    to kill your pet and summon a new one than die because you were not paying attention.</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small><strong>Are
    all my pets the same?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>No.&nbsp; Each pet is unique in
    it's abilities.&nbsp; You may want to read <strong><a
    href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/misc/pages/gzmagi.asp'>GZ's Article on Magicians</a></strong>
    which explains the difference between them.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small><strong>Is
    there anything I can do to lower my spell resist rate?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>Yes.&nbsp; Magicians get two
    spells, Malise and Malisement.&nbsp; Both of these lower the enemies ability to resist
    your spells.&nbsp; They also stack with the Enchanter Tashan series.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18' bgcolor='#0E024D'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Arial'><small><strong>What are focus objects?</strong></small></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width='100%' height='18'><font face='Arial'><small>Magicians get two
    different focus objects.  One set is obtained through quests in the temple of Solusek Ro.  The others, Mastery Objects, are obtained off high level creatures.  Focus objects give you pets extra hit points and enchance the stats in the natural abilities.  They also make your pet appear larger.  They do NOT make your pet attack faster, you must use Burnout for this.</small></font></td>
  </tr>
</table>
